-vf harddup -af lavcresample=48000:channels=2 -srate 48000 -ofps 25 -of mpeg -mpegopts format=mpeg2:tsaf"/></nowiki>
}}
* Set the '''<accept-url>''' element to '''yes''' for the '''video2mpeg''' profile.
{{File|/etc/mediatomb/config.xml||
 <nowiki>
        <accept-url></nowiki>'''yes'''<nowiki></accept-url></nowiki>
}}
* Install MPlayer.
{{Note|The {{Package|media-video/mplayer|direct=yes}} '''encode''' USE flag needs to be enabled for transcoding support.}}
{{RootCmd|emerge -av media-video/mplayer}}

===DLNA===
{{Note|MediaTomb doesn't implement the [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Digital_Living_Network_Alliance DLNA] specification and is not a DLNA media server. It does however offer basic support for some DLNA devices e.g. PlayStation 3}}
* To enable DLNA support, set the '''extend''' attribute to '''yes''' for the '''<protocolInfo>''' element.
{{File|/etc/mediatomb/config.xml||
 <nowiki>
    <protocolInfo extend="</nowiki>'''yes'''<nowiki>"/></nowiki>
}}
* If you have a DLNA enabled TV (e.g. Samsung), add the following section in between the '''<server>''' and '''</server>''' elements.
{{File|/etc/mediatomb/config.xml||
 <nowiki>
    <custom-http-headers>
      <add header="transferMode.dlna.org: Streaming"/>
      <add header="contentFeatures.dlna.org: DLNA.ORG_OP=01;DLNA.ORG_CI=0;DLNA.ORG_FLAGS=01500000000000000000000000000000"/>
    </custom-http-headers></nowiki>
}}

===Online Services===
MediaTomb allows you to stream online content to your UPnP device from services such as [http://www.youtube.com/ YouTube]. For more information, please consult Section 6.2.1 of the [http://mediatomb.cc/pages/documentation MediaTomb] documentation.

====YouTube====
{{Warning|There are reports on the MediaTomb [http://sourceforge.net/projects/mediatomb/forums/forum/440751/topic/4013201 forum] that YouTube support is currently broken.}}
{{Note|You need to specify the content you want to view, as the default Gentoo configuration file only provides a sample. For more information, please consult Section 6.2.2 of the [http://mediatomb.cc/pages/documentation MediaTomb] documentation.}}
* To enable YouTube support, set the '''enabled''' attribute to '''yes''' for the '''<YouTube>''' element.
{{File|/etc/mediatomb/config.xml||
 <nowiki>
      <YouTube enabled="</nowiki>'''yes'''<nowiki>" refresh="28800" update-at-start="yes" purge-after="604800" racy-content="exclude" format="mp4" hd="no"></nowiki>
}}
* If you want to view YouTube videos in high definition (if available), set the '''hd''' attribute to '''yes''' for the '''<YouTube>''' element.
{{File|/etc/mediatomb/config.xml||
 <nowiki>
      <YouTube enabled="yes" refresh="28800" update-at-start="yes" purge-after="604800" racy-content="exclude" format="mp4" hd="</nowiki>'''yes'''<nowiki>"></nowiki>
}}
* If your UPnP device doesn't support MP4 videos, enable [[MediaTomb#Transcoding|transcoding]] and add the following section in between the '''<mimetype-profile-mappings>''' and '''</mimetype-profile-mappings>''' elements.
{{File|/etc/mediatomb/config.xml||
 <nowiki>
      <transcode mimetype="video/mp4" using="video2mpeg"/></nowiki>
}}

===Video Thumbnails===
{{Note|The {{Package|net-misc/mediatomb|direct=yes}} '''ffmpeg''' and '''thumbnail''' USE flags need to be enabled for video thumbnail support.}}
* To enable video thumbnail support, set the '''enabled''' attribute to '''yes''' for the '''<ffmpegthumbnailer>''' element.
{{File|/etc/mediatomb/config.xml||
 <nowiki>
      <ffmpegthumbnailer enabled="</nowiki>'''yes'''<nowiki>"></nowiki>
}}
* If you want to overlay a filmstrip border on the generated thumbnail, set the '''<filmstrip-overlay>''' element to '''yes'''.
{{File|/etc/mediatomb/config.xml||
 <nowiki>
        <filmstrip-overlay></nowiki>'''yes'''<nowiki></filmstrip-overlay></nowiki>
}}
* If you have a DLNA enabled device that supports video thumbnails (e.g. PlayStation 3), set the '''extend''' attribute to '''yes''' for the '''<protocolInfo>''' element.
{{File|/etc/mediatomb/config.xml||
 <nowiki>
    <protocolInfo extend="</nowiki>'''yes'''<nowiki>"/></nowiki>
}}

===Raw Images===
* To enable (Canon CR2 and Nikon NEF) [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Raw_image_format raw image] support, enable [[MediaTomb#Transcoding|transcoding]] and add the following section in between the '''<profile>''' and '''</profile>''' elements.
{{File|/etc/mediatomb/config.xml||
 <nowiki>
      <profile name="raw2jpeg" enabled="yes" type="external">
        <mimetype>image/jpeg</mimetype>
        <accept-url>no</accept-url>
        <first-resource>yes</first-resource>
        <hide-original-resource>yes</hide-original-resource>
        <use-chunked-encoding>no</use-chunked-encoding>
        <agent command="/usr/local/bin/mediatomb-raw2jpeg" arguments="%in %out"/>
        <buffer size="524288" chunk-size="512" fill-size="1024"/>
      </profile></nowiki>
}}
* Add the following section in between the '''<mimetype-profile-mappings>''' and '''</mimetype-profile-mappings>''' elements.
{{File|/etc/mediatomb/config.xml||
 <nowiki>
      <transcode mimetype="image/raw" using="raw2jpeg"/></nowiki>
}}
* For every additional raw image format (supported by [http://www.cybercom.net/~dcoffin/dcraw/ dcraw]), add the following section in between the '''<extension-mimetype ignore-unknown&#61;"no">''' and '''</extension-mimetype>''' elements and substitute '''extension''' with the appropriate value e.g. <map from&#61;"'''kdc'''" to&#61;"image/raw"/>
{{File|/etc/mediatomb/config.xml||
 <nowiki>
        <map from="</nowiki>'''extension'''<nowiki>" to="image/raw"/></nowiki>
}}
* Create the following script.
{{File|/usr/local/bin/mediatomb-raw2jpeg||
 <nowiki>
#!/bin/bash

DCRAW_PATH="/usr/bin/dcraw"
INPUT="$1"
OUTPUT="$2"

exec "${DCRAW_PATH}" -e -c "${INPUT}" > "${OUTPUT}"</nowiki>
}}
* Install dcraw.
{{RootCmd|emerge -av media-gfx/dcraw}}

